Periscope

The purpose of the periscope is to bring the beam from one point and propagation direction to another without introducing any changes to the beam itself. In NL-2p1 microscope, the scanner module, which follows the periscope, includes an input kinematic mirror, so requirements to the precision of the alignment of the periscope are somewhat alleviated. However, it's still good practice to make sure that the beam hits each mirror at the center, as it simplifies the regular checks of the microscope alignment. For this purpose, the periscope presented here includes extra rods used exclusively for the alignment of the system.
